main event: A dull orange object was observed for 1 minute and 30 seconds on June 15, 1963, in the South Pacific Ocean from San Jose, California.
interesting points: The observation was made in clear weather conditions with heavy haze over San Jose., The object maneuvered and was concluded to be partially balloon and partially aircraft., The sighting lasted for 1 minute and 30 seconds., The observer claimed to be a qualified Army/Navy observer., There was a total of one object observed during this incident.
